<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4688200>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 2. — Heurtaultia rossiorum n. gen., n. sp., holotype male: A, carapace (incomplete), foreshortened posterodorsal view, with detail (× 4) of granulation on mesozone; B, coxae of palp and legs (incomplete), anteroventral view; C, left chelicera, dorso-antiaxial view. Abbreviations: b, es, is, gs, ls, sb, setae of chelicera; ml, median maxillary lyrifissure; pl, posterior maxillary lyrifissure. Scale bars: A, B, 0.3 mm; C, 0.1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4688200/files/figure.png" .

